title: Spanish La Liga Table & Results: Points Table and Team Standings at 2015-16 Spanish League Week 9
text:
Spanish La Liga Table & Results: Points Table and Team Standings at 2015-16 Spanish League Week 9 By India.com Sports Desk on October 19, 2015 at 9:43 PM Comments 
Spanish La Liga’s duopoly continued and it was indeed Real Madrid and Barcelona continued to rule the roost with comprehensive victories. Atletico Madrid are hot on the heels of the league leaders and there are only two points behind after snatching a point in Madrid derby last week. David Moyes is under a lot of scrutiny after the poor start that Real Sociedad have got off to. 
Barcelona have got off to a slightly scratchy start but are well and truly in the title race with Neymar stepping up in Lionel Messi’s absence. The Brazilian forward netted four goals over the weekend. Goals and Cristiano Ronaldo walk hand in hand and the Portuguese maverick became Real Madrid’s highest ever goalscorer, beating the record held by Raul. The 10-time European champions raced to a 3-0 win against Levante and have now grabbed pole position in the league.
